**Explanation:** Food security, as defined by the **FAO (Food and Agriculture Organization)**, encompasses **availability, access, utilization, and stability** of food to ensure all people have sufficient, safe, and nutritious food at all times. While options like **F** (access) or **I** (production) are partially correct, **C** is the most comprehensive and widely accepted definition. Other options (e.g., price control, biosecurity, or GMOs) are narrower or unrelated to the core concept.
